            <h2>How You Can Help</h2>
            <p>Thinking of ways to reduce your carbon footprint? Here are some simple green tips, because every single bit counts!</p>
            <p><strong class="underline">Save on Electricity:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Turn off the lights when you leave a room.</li>
                <li>Switch to Energy Efficient compact florescent bulbs.</li>
                <li>Use solar lights for outside lighting.</li>
                <li>Use time based temperature control thermostats to ensure reduction in temperature when you are away from home and comfortable settings when you are in.</li>
                <li>Ensure that your doors and windows are sealed tightly during winter to avoid energy waste.</li>
                <li>Close the rooms that you don’t use. If you have multiple thermostat zones, reduce the thermostat temperature setting without risking freezing of pipes.</li>
                <li>Unplug appliances when not in use.</li>
                <li>Line dry clothes when the weather permits.</li>
                <li>Run the dishwasher and washer-dryer for full loads.</li>
                <li>Use energy efficient appliances.</li>
                <li>Take shorter showers.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong class="underline">Commute:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use public transport where available.</li>
                <li>Plan errands and grocery shopping to avoid multiple trips.</li>
                <li>Buy locally grown food.</li>
                <li>Share a ride to work.</li>
                <li>Drive fuel-efficient cars.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong class="underline">Recycle:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Avoid buying bottled water. Use water-purifying filters instead. Use reusable water bottles.</li>
                <li>Buy in bulk when possible. This reduces packaging wastes.</li>
                <li>Use cell phones, computers and other appliances as long as possible. Recycle them responsibly.</li>
                <li>Recycle milk cartons, paper products and other items that are marked for recycling.</li>
                <li>Participate in your local or township recycle initiatives.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong class="underline">Volunteer with Tavas:</strong></p>
            <p>Be a green advocate and volunteer your skills at Tavas. We are always looking for volunteers from all walks of life. If you have the will, we have the way! <a href="JoinUs.aspx">Join</a> our hands and together we can make a difference.</p>
            <p><strong class="underline">Join Us on Facebook and Twitter:</strong></p>
            <p>Are you a social network bee? Follow the buzz and promote our cause on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Tavas-Its-Your-Power-Own-It/172366689470665" target="_blank" title="Facebook">Facebook</a> and <a href="http://www.twitter.com/TavasPower" target="_blank" title="Twitter">Twitter</a>.</p>
